The rear tyres were modelled based on Pacejka’s ‘Magic Formula’ or semi-empirical tyre model for car tyres. Due to the limiting testing facilities available, the Similarity Method [18] was used to determine the parameters. This method is based on the observation that the pure slip curves remain approximately similar in shape when the tyre runs at conditions that are different from the reference condition. For the purposes of this study, the reference condition is defined as the state where the tyre runs at its nominal load (
